.TH "kvm_get_badinstr" 9 "kvm_get_badinstr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kvm_get_badinstr \- Get bad instruction encoding.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kvm_get_badinstr
.BI "(u32 *opc "  ","
.BI "struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu "  ","
.BI "u32 *out "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "opc" 12
Guest pointer to faulting instruction.
.IP "vcpu" 12
KVM VCPU information.
.IP "out" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Gets the instruction encoding of the faulting instruction, using the saved
BadInstr register value if it exists, otherwise falling back to reading guest
memory at \fIopc\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
The instruction encoding of the faulting instruction.
